Author: Kevin Klues <kklues@nvidia.com>
Date:   Wed Aug 19 12:15:34 2020 -0700

    Add setup_mig_minor_cgroups() to enable cgroups for MIG devices on a GPU

    This is necessary to make the mig-confg and mig-monitor capabilities
    useful. With /proc based capabilities all we had to do was bind-mount a
    directory from /proc in order to give the container access to _all_
    capabilities from that subtree down. This is required to ensure that a
    container has access to any GPU devices that are reated / destroyed
    after the container has already started.

    With /dev based capabilities it is not as straight-forward. We now have
    to enumerate all possible capabilities under a subtree and give the
    container acess to each of them individually. We have designed it so
    that the minor ids for the set of capabilities that exist under any
    given tree in /proc is predetermined and stored in a file under
    /proc/nvidia-caps/*-minors. We use the file mig-minors for our purposes
    here.

    Signed-off-by: Kevin Klues <kklues@nvidia.com>
