    Conditionally list/mount MIG monitor/config capabilities

    Previously we would attempt to list/mount the global MIG config/monitor
    capabilities anytime the --mig-monitor=all or --mig-config=all flags
    were passed to the 'info' or 'configure' CLI commands. This was fine on
    machines that had at least one MIG capable GPU on them. However, on
    systems that have no MIG capable GPUs this would cause problems (because
    the files representing these capabilities simply don't exist!)

    Since we want to allow the same configuration to work on any system
    (whether it has MIG capable GPUs on it or not), we now skip
    listing/mounting these files if there are no MIG capable GPUs visible.

